Here's an example script that recursively goes through the files in the `pages` directory, generates a flat file path, and declares a map between the file path and the type of the module exported by the file:
```
import fs from "fs";
import path from "path";

// Declare the map object that will store the file path to module type mapping
const filePathToModuleType: { [filePath: string]: any } = {};

// Helper function to convert a file path to a flat file path in the format
// specified in the prompt. This function uses the regex provided in the prompt.
function convertFilePathToFlatFilePath(filePath: string) {
  return filePath
    .replace(/\.\/pages|index|\.tsx$/g, "")
    .replace(/\[\.{3}.+\]/, "*")
    .replace(/\[(.+)\]/, ":$1")
    .replace(/^\//, "")
    .replace(/\/$/, "");
}

// Helper function to recursively go through the files in the `pages` directory
// and generate the file path to module type mapping.
function generateFilePathToModuleTypeMapping(dir: string) {
  // Read the contents of the directory
  const files = fs.readdirSync(dir);

  // Loop through the files in the directory
  for (const file of files) {
    // Get the full file path
    const filePath = path.join(dir, file);

    // Check if the file is a directory
    if (fs.lstatSync(filePath).isDirectory()) {
      // If it's a directory, recursively call this function
      // to process the files in the directory
      generateFilePathToModuleTypeMapping(filePath);
    } else {
      // If it's a file, check if it's a TypeScript file
      if (filePath.endsWith(".tsx")) {
        // If it's a TypeScript file, import the module and
        // get the type of the default export
        const module = require(filePath);
        const moduleType = typeof module.default;

        // Convert the file path to a flat file path
        const flatFilePath = convertFilePathToFlatFilePath(filePath);

        // Add an entry to the map with the flat file path as the key
        // and the module type as the value
        filePathToModuleType[flatFilePath] = moduleType;
      }
    }
  }
}

// Start the recursive processing of the files in the `pages` directory
generateFilePathToModuleTypeMapping("./pages");

// Print the map object
console.log(filePathToModuleType);
```
This script uses the `fs` module to read the files in the `pages` directory, and the `path` module to join file paths. It also uses the `require` function to import the modules and get the type of the default export.

The script generates a map object that stores the file path to module type mapping, and prints the map object to the console. You can use this map object to generate the TypeScript declaration file.

